track_notes:
This 2.83 mile long track begins at the turn-off from W Manville Rd at GPS 32.28991,-111.38646. It took me about a half hour to drive this distance. Some words of advice:
1. A high ground clearance vehicle is necessary. 
2. Your vehicle will get pinstriped by the bushes on the narrow jeep tracks encountered.
3. Remove all antennas from the vehicle as trees hang low over the jeep trails in many places and could snap off an antenna.
4. Avoid the area during monsoon season as roads and trails do flood.
track_title: How to Drive to Laughing Leos Hill

track_notes: Expect a typical desert bushwhack with lots of cactus, big boulders, steep sections, loose scree, barbed wire fences, etc. The distance to the summit from where I parked is about a mile, with most of the elevation gain occurring in the last half mile. It took me almost an hour to ascend with a 43-lb pack of radio gear.
track_title: K9PM Ascent of Laughing Leos Hill W7A/PE-114

track_notes: The track for my descent from Laughing Leos Hill is fairly close to the track for the ascent. It took me just as long to descend as it did to ascend, a little less than one hour.
track_title: K9PM Descent from Laughing Leos Hill W7A/PE-114
